replies.body:
The most annoying ability in the game is "No Mana".

Why does that champ get to dump out skills and dashes and sustain that are all better than mine and have no cost?

Acceptable No Mana Champs: {{champion:154}} {{champion:8}} {{champion:98}} {{champion:68}} {{champion:82}} {{champion:150}} {{champion:36}} {{champion:266}} 

Unnaceptable

(Replace Energy with Mana Bar)
{{champion:85}} {{champion:84}} {{champion:64}} {{champion:238}} 

(If They have a "Rage" resource add a 3rd bar for Mana, balance costs accordingly)
{{champion:23}} {{champion:107}} {{champion:58}} 

(If no resource at all, explain why their kit warrants infinite / less skillful play with superior benefits)
{{champion:157}} {{champion:92}} {{champion:55}} 


*These champs arent all broken or low skill champs but its just the idea that this champion has no resource with no explanation as to why is what bothers me. There are plenty of OP skills in the game but the most OP will always be "No Resource" and nowadays its being thrown on every new champ. It promotes less thought in Build Paths and Item Order. It promotes less skill/counterplay. And most of all its not as if these are weak champs with weaker output to balance their infinite harass, mobility, free saves on mistakes, sustain. To be honest most of the time these Manaless champs are not going to have to worry about keeping their resources up early game, they usually will outsustain you either naturally or with a first item sustain. And also most of the time they will also have lower cooldowns and be among the highest damage outputers in the game.

These are all amongst the top tier damage output champs (When built Damage) with relatively low cooldowns and relatively high mobility. Some of which can also be tanky as well. Not all OP but all need to come with an explanation as to why they can be given an additional or replacement bar of mana with low costs to balance their rage bars.
